Description: CVE-2026-32882 - Fix overlay image with alpha channels using wrong stride
 When computing the alpha value during image overlay, the code incorrectly
 uses in_stride (the stride of the color channel) instead of alpha_stride
 (the stride of the alpha channel). When these strides differ, this causes
 an out-of-bounds read.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/strukturag/libheif/commit/22b6266bf03a9f016f84a9b57b80e1dd7c79d64a
Author: Dirk Farin <dirk.farin@gmail.com>
